By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The state Chairman peoples Democratic Party, Barr. Charles Ezekwem has resigned his position in the Party. Ezekwe who based his resignation on what he called “prevailing circumstance” within the party, also denounced his membership of the party. He disclosed this on Sunday in a letter addressed to the National Chairman Of the Party, made available to Sundiata Post. See the letter below: 